         <abstract>
            <p>
               In this paper, we show that the main results of the local convergence theory for least-change secant update methods of Dennis and Walker (SIAM J. Numer. Anal. 18 (1981), 949-987) can be proved using the theory introduced recently by Martínez (Math. Comp. 55 (1990), 143-167). In addition, we exhibit two generalizations of well-known methods whose local convergence can be easily proved using Martínez's theory. 
            </p>
          </abstract>
